abstract: This was a caucus like Iowans had never seen before: Voters from Egypt, Italy, Amsterdam and beyond descended on a Paris town hall Monday to choose their Democratic candidate for the 2020 election.
snippet: This was a caucus like Iowans had never seen before: Voters from Egypt, Italy, Amsterdam and beyond descended on a Paris town hall Monday to choose their Democratic candidate for the 2020 election.
lead_paragraph: PARIS — This was a caucus like Iowans had never seen before: Voters from Egypt, Italy, Amsterdam and beyond descended on a Paris town hall Monday to choose their Democratic candidate for the 2020 election.
headline_main: Iowan Voters Converge on Paris, and Make Electoral History
headline_print_headline: Iowan Voters Converge on Paris, and Make Electoral History

abstract: Ms. Murkowski had joined the overwhelming majority of her conference in blocking consideration of new witnesses and documents.
snippet: Ms. Murkowski had joined the overwhelming majority of her conference in blocking consideration of new witnesses and documents.
lead_paragraph: Senator Lisa Murkowski, Republican of Alaska, announced on Monday that she would vote to acquit President Trump, acknowledging that while the president’s pressure campaign against Ukraine was inappropriate, it did not rise to the level of removing a president from office.
headline_main: Senator Lisa Murkowski says she will vote to acquit President Trump.
byline_original: By Emily Cochrane and Catie Edmondson

abstract: Shaun Donovan, a former cabinet secretary, files paperwork to run for mayor.
snippet: Shaun Donovan, a former cabinet secretary, files paperwork to run for mayor.
lead_paragraph: Shaun Donovan, a former housing secretary and budget director under President Barack Obama, filed paperwork on Monday to run for mayor of New York City.

abstract: A humanitarian channel to bring food and medicine to Iran has started trial operations, the Swiss and U.S. governments said on Thursday, helping supply Swiss goods to the struggling population without tripping over U.S. sanctions.
snippet: A humanitarian channel to bring food and medicine to Iran has started trial operations, the Swiss and U.S. governments said on Thursday, helping supply Swiss goods to the struggling population without tripping over U.S. sanctions.
lead_paragraph: ZURICH/WASHINGTON — A humanitarian channel to bring food and medicine to Iran has started trial operations, the Swiss and U.S. governments said on Thursday, helping supply Swiss goods to the struggling population without tripping over U.S. sanctions.
headline_main: U.S. Says First Shipments of Medicine to Iran Delivered via Swiss Humanitarian Channel

abstract: Taiwan's vice president-elect William Lai will go to this week's high-profile National Prayer Breakfast in Washington, he said on Monday, an event traditionally attended by U.S. presidents and which President Donald Trump was at last year.

abstract: Iowa Democrats are fiercely united by the goal of unseating President Donald Trump, but they were sharply divided Monday over which candidate was best equipped to do so, according to the AP VoteCast survey.

abstract: Texas A&M University won't create filters on Facebook that target animal rights activists under a lawsuit settlement that ends another court case surrounding the First Amendment in the age of social media.
